## Phase 2 — Introspect the Live Database

> Load `references/mongo-mcp-tools.md` before any call.

The reason to introspect before coding: field names in MongoDB are often different from what
you’d guess (snake_case vs camelCase, abbreviations, legacy names). Getting these wrong means
@Field annotations are missing and queries silently return nothing.

Run these in order:

```
1. list_collections(db_name)
   → Exact collection names for @Document(collection = "...")

2. find(db, collection, filter={}, limit=3, sort={createdAt:-1})   ← per collection
   → Real field names, real types, real nesting. This is ground truth.

3. list_indexes(db, collection)   ← per collection
   → Every index = a @Indexed or @CompoundIndex needed in Java

4. count_documents(db, collection, {})
   → >10K docs → Pageable mandatory on all repo methods

5. aggregate($lookup)   ← only when cross-collection relations suspected
   → Confirm the relation actually works in the DB

6. aggregate($group by status/type/category fields)
   → Get all real enum values before defining the Java enum
```

Relation patterns decoded from sampled documents:

```
"userId": "64abc..."       → Manual Reference  — store String, join in service
"address": { "city":... }  → Embedded Document — POJO without @Document
"items": [{ "sku":... }]   → Embedded List     — List<ItemPojo>
"tagIds": ["a","b"]        → Ref List          — List<String>
"$ref"/"$id" pattern       → DBRef (legacy)    — do NOT replicate, warn user
```

